# thoth appliance environment — copy to /home/pkm/.thoth/.env, fill in real values,
# `chmod 600`, and keep it OUT of git. The systemd units (deploy/*.service) load it via
# EnvironmentFile. Lines are plain KEY=value (no `export`, no quotes needed).

# --- vault + home ---------------------------------------------------------------------
PKM_VAULT=/opt/pkm-vault
OBSIDIAN_VAULT_NAME=pkm-vault
THOTH_HOME=/home/pkm/.thoth

# --- Hindsight semantic index ---------------------------------------------------------
# Hindsight runs as a standalone `hindsight-api` HTTP server (the deploy/thoth-hindsight
# .service unit). thoth talks to it as a plain HTTP client; the bank id is a path segment
# on every retain/recall. THOTH_HINDSIGHT_BASE_URL points at the server (default below);
# THOTH_HINDSIGHT_BANK selects the bank. The server's OWN config (LLM provider/model/key,
# embeddings, Postgres) lives in a separate file the server reads, NOT here — see
# deploy/hindsight-api.env.example.
# THOTH_HINDSIGHT_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8888
THOTH_HINDSIGHT_BANK=thoth

# --- models ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL is the default for every call. THOTH_ANALYSE_MODEL (the folded
# analyse/kind/transcription vision call), THOTH_DIAGRAM_MODEL (the Excalidraw
# reconstruction call), and THOTH_INTENT_MODEL (the free-text intent gate) override it
# per-call; unset = fall back to ANTHROPIC_MODEL (the intent gate falls back to a cheap
# Haiku). The diagram reconstruction wants strong spatial reasoning, so Opus is worth it;
# the intent gate is a one-shot routing call, so a cheap model is the point.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6
# THOTH_ANALYSE_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6
# THOTH_INTENT_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5
THOTH_DIAGRAM_MODEL=claude-opus-4-8

# THOTH_MAX_ANALYSE_IMAGES caps how many images a multi-image batch sends to the ONE
# shared vision call (default 6; extras beyond the cap are still saved + embedded, just
# not analysed). A non-positive value analyses every image.
# THOTH_MAX_ANALYSE_IMAGES=6

# --- research/extraction (optional) ---------------------------------------------------
# EXA_API_KEY + FIRECRAWL_API_KEY power the blended `research:` path (web search +
# URL->Markdown). Leave blank to run vault-only. (Hindsight's own LLM/embedding keys live
# in deploy/hindsight-api.env.example, not here — thoth does not call the index backend.)
EXA_API_KEY=
FIRECRAWL_API_KEY=

# --- vault git sync -------------------------------------------------------------------
GITHUB_PKM_VAULT_TOKEN=ghp_...

# --- Slack ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=xoxb-...
SLACK_APP_TOKEN=xapp-...
# SLACK_ALLOWED_USERS is the member id (starts with `U…`), NOT the DM/channel id (`D…`).
SLACK_ALLOWED_USERS=U0123456789
SLACK_SUMMARY_CHANNEL=C0123456789
SLACK_CAPTURE_CHANNEL=C0123456789

# --- MCP HTTP transport (optional, issue #103) ----------------------------------------
# Only needed when you run the remote MCP surface (`thoth mcp --transport http`, the
# thoth-mcp.service unit). Leave UNSET for the local stdio transport (`thoth mcp`), which
# Claude Code spawns as a child and which needs no key.
#
# Tier 1 — static bearer (REQUIRED for HTTP). Comma-separated; every HTTP request must
# carry `Authorization: Bearer <one-of-these>`. Multiple keys support rotation (add a new
# one, let clients cut over, drop the old one). The server FAILS FAST at startup if this
# is unset — it never binds an unauthenticated socket. Generate with e.g.
# `python -c 'import secrets; print(secrets.token_urlsafe(32))'`.
# THOTH_MCP_API_KEYS=<key-one>,<key-two>
#
# Tier 2 — Cloudflare-Access JWT (OPTIONAL defense-in-depth, OFF unless BOTH are set).
# When set, the origin ALSO validates the `Cf-Access-Jwt-Assertion` header that
# cloudflared adds (signature against the team JWKS, `aud`, `exp`). See ADR 0011 and
# docs/how-to/mcp-server-setup.md for the cloudflared + Access wiring.
# THOTH_MCP_CF_ACCESS_TEAM_DOMAIN=<your-team>.cloudflareaccess.com
# THOTH_MCP_CF_ACCESS_AUD=<your-access-application-aud-tag>
#
# DNS-rebinding allowlist (OPTIONAL). FastMCP's streamable-HTTP guard accepts only
# loopback Host/Origin headers by default, so the public hostname forwarded by cloudflared
# 421s unless you either set `httpHostHeader: localhost:8765` in the tunnel ingress
# (preferred) OR append the public names here (comma-separated; kept alongside the
# loopback defaults). See docs/how-to/mcp-server-setup.md.
# THOTH_MCP_ALLOWED_HOSTS=<public-hostname>
# THOTH_MCP_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://<public-hostname>
#
# Tier 3 — OAuth 2.1 + PKCE (OPTIONAL, per-user GitHub identity for non-browser MCP
# clients like the claude.ai connector and `claude mcp add --transport http`). The static
# THOTH_MCP_API_KEYS bearer above keeps working in parallel for scripts/cron. OAuth
# activates only when ALL FOUR required vars are set (a partial set is a startup error);
# THOTH_ALLOWED_GITHUB_USERS is the only authorization control, re-checked on every token.
# Create a GitHub OAuth App with callback URL https://<public-hostname>/callback. See
# docs/how-to/mcp-oauth.md.
# GITHUB_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=<github-oauth-app-client-id>
# GITHUB_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=<github-oauth-app-client-secret>
# THOTH_JWT_SIGNING_SECRET=<openssl rand -hex 32>
# THOTH_ALLOWED_GITHUB_USERS=<your-github-login>,<another-github-login>
# THOTH_OAUTH_SERVER_URL=https://<public-hostname>
